When I configure log4j using an object of java.util.Properties with default 
values in it, some default properties are not found.

In org.apache.log4j.config.PropertySetter the method
void setProperties(Properties properties, String prefix) uses 
properties.getKey() to get a Enumeration of the keys in the property list.
I changed it to properties.propertyNames() to get the keys of the default 
values too.

I changed the code in the following way and after this change my code works.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
[...]

  public
  void setProperties(Properties properties, String prefix) {
    int len = prefix.length();

// original code
//  for (Enumeration e = properties.keys(); e.hasMoreElements(); ) {
//
// fixed code
    for (Enumeration e = properties.propertyNames(); e.hasMoreElements(); ) {
      String key = (String) e.nextElement();

[...]
